{"key":"post-12382191","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>12382191</id>\n<content>Make it air tight.&amp;nbsp; You don't want leakage of air around the HEPA filter. Build a plenum at least as large as the filter, to equalize pressure on the back side. That blower and filter combo should be fine.&amp;nbsp; You might end up wanting a motor speed controller, as about 200 cfm to 250 cfm is what you'll want out the front.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;I do LOTS of large spawn bags with a 12 X 24 flowhood, about 4,000 in the last three months.&amp;nbsp; You do G2G with the receiving bag laying on its side to keep it in the sterile air flow.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>12382272</next>\n<prev>12382116</prev>\n<first>12379669</first>\n<last>12578952</last>\n<when>1271134812</when>\n<utime>04/13/10 08:00 AM</utime>\n</post>"}